    "Designers can then evaluate the generated solutions against the main requirements, ending the design process if they are satisfied (Zeng and Gu, 1999a).",
    "Several studies have analyzed the strengths and weaknesses of both TRIZ and EBD.",
    "The findings indicate that while TRIZ excels in the synthesis stage (solution generation), it lacks systematic tools to assist designers in problem redefinition (Ilevbare et al., 2013; Mohammadi et al., 2022).",
    "Conversely, EBD is well-equipped with effective tools for problem processing and knowledge gathering (problem redefinition) but lacks strong ideation tools (Dubois et al., 2012).",
    "Therefore, integrating these two design methodologies could establish a comprehensive design framework."
  ],
